     Key => "1.3.13",
     Headline => "computation in quotient rings",
     "In Macaulay2, we define a quotient ring using the usual mathematical
     notation.",
     EXAMPLE {
	  "R = ZZ/32003[x,y,z];",
	  "Q = R/(x^2+y^2-z^5, z-x-y^2)",
	  "f = z^2+y^2",
	  "g = z^2+2*x-2*z-3*z^5+3*x^2+6*y^2",
